197 outside of a time frame specified by the parent or legal
198 guardian.
199 b. Limit the covered minor's access to any portion of
200 such covered operator's covered platform that recommends,
201 selects, or prioritizes media items in the manner set forth in
202 subdivision (b)(1) to a maximum daily period specified by the
203 parent or legal guardian.
204 c. Set the covered minor's covered platform account to
205 a mode that exclusively allows users to whom the covered minor
206 is connected to view or respond to content posted by the
207 covered minor.
208 (d) Not later than March 1, 2028, and annually
209 thereafter, each covered operator shall publicly disclose, in
210 a form and manner specified by the Attorney General, all of
211 the following information for the preceding calendar year:
212 (1) The total number of covered users who used the
213 covered operator's covered platform during the year.
214 (2) The portion of the total number of covered users
215 who used the covered operator's covered platform during the
216 year for whom the covered operator obtained verifiable consent
217 from a parent or legal guardian.
218 (3) The portion of the total number of covered users
219 who used the covered operator's covered platform for whom the
220 default settings set forth in subdivision (c)(2) were enabled,
221 and the portion of the total number of covered users for whom
222 such default settings were not enabled.
223 (4) The average amount of time per day that covered
224 users used the covered operator's covered platform, broken
Page 8

users used the covered operator's covered platform, broken
HB173 INTRODUCED
225 down by user age and hour of day.
226 (e) Nothing in this section shall be construed to do
227 any of the following:
228 (1) Require a covered operator to provide a covered
229 minor's parent or legal guardian with access to, or control
230 over, the covered minor's covered platform account or any data
231 associated therewith, unless provision of such access or
232 control is specifically required by this section.
233 (2) Impose liability for any commercial activity or
234 action by a covered operator subject to 15 U.S.C. § 6501 which
235 is inconsistent with the manner in which the commercial
236 activity or action is treated under 15 U.S.C. § 6502.
237 (f) A violation of this section shall be deemed a
238 violation of the Deceptive Trade Practices Act, pursuant to
239 Chapter 19 of Title 8, Code of Alabama 1975.
240 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
241 1, 2026.
